        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "δούλας",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " do not mean those of servile rank, but are applied in a general sense to those who are worshippers, and so servants of God. But in retaining the word ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "μου",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " we are not obliged to reject the literal meaning “bond-servants,” just as St. Peter himself, in addressing household servants and slaves, commands them to act ",
